Best sudoku app. Granular difficulty, properly made puzzles, extensive training in solving techniques, from beginning to advanced, endlessly new puzzles even if offline. Biggest downfall is UI and lack of updates, but everything else more than makes up for it. Can't recommend highly enough

It's not the prettiest app, and hasn't been updated since 2015, but it's the best Sudoku by far. Pencil options, new daily puzzles, hints and auto solver even for user-entered games (like one you found in the paper or something), tons of features, difficulty levels, and even training. If you want to learn how to use a Sashimi X-wing to solve puzzles, this app will tell you. Though I still don't understand it :-D. Definitely worth paying for. Also, no ads!
I love this game, the only game I play!!

great game

One of the OG games I put on my first smart phone that has consistently been on every smart phone I have had since. What makes this app stand out from all the other sudoku apps is the plethora of difficulty levels you can choose from. I love it!!
A faultless 5 Star app in every way! It's training, manual, practice games tailored to my developing skills! Wonderful! Truly wonderful!

I have used this app nightly for years but after wiping my phone, I checked out all the latest (and much prettier) sudoku apps only to discover they are all *significantly* inferior to this one. This app has slowly taught me how to play at an advanced level, ranking together puzzles that require the same advanced techniques to solve so that you eventually become proficient at them by playing the same level over and over. I never spend money on apps but this one is worth it.
BEST Sudoku ever!
It is a Very good game that I purchased. It got recently updated .

Smart interface, learning oriented. Most Sudoku games are glorified editors. Appearance and interface are the only differences between them. If you ask for a hint they fill in the next number. This app walks you through solving strategies, from simple to quite complex. It teaches you to see relationships that you would not have figured out. If you think Sudoku ever involves guessing, this app has things to teach you.

The all round best sudoku app, and has been for years. It hasn't been updated for years because it hasn't needed to be. If you want intuitive play, granular choices of difficulty, excellent tutorials for techniques from absolute beginner through to prodigy, and well thought out options for how hints (they start vague and get more specific if you need more help), pencil marks and automatic behaviour (eg automatic removal of pencil marks) are managed, stop looking. You've found the sudoku grail.
I have enjoyed this game very much through the years.
Love it, but getting virus alert. Won't use till report says ok.

Detecting viruses is an extremely complicated business, and false positives will inevitably occur occasionally.

I emailed the developer a couple of months ago, to which he responded, acknowledging the situation, but no resolution has been forthcoming. A resolution will return this app to five stars, which it otherwise deserves. Still no resolution from the developer so I am churlishly decreasing my rating to one star in the hope of attracting the developer's attention to rectify the problem. My one star instead attracted Samsung's attention, and thanks to an android update the problem is now resolved. The developer has got away with it.

replyContent: Certain newer versions of Android were not allowing our app to load user photos as menu backgrounds. There is supposed to be a way to do it without that permission, but on certain versions of Android on specific devices that procedure was just not working correctly unless the app had full permission to read photos.

content: Why does the latest version require access to photos, etc.!!!! I've paid for the app. I don't want to be spied upon!!!
replyContent: Newer versions of Android need access to User Photos in order to load them as menu backgrounds. Working around bugs in the import procedure needs this permission on a few of the most popular devices, so at this time, we have decided to ask for the permission.

I've tried a bunch of sudoku apps but this one is definitely the best. It automatically deletes your pencils when you fill in a box, entry is super fast, and you can choose to have to warn about all errors, just illogical entries, or go with no help at all.  You can even have it do the pencil work for you, if you're feeling particularly lazy. I also love that it tells you how well you did compared to other players.

I freely admit that I am a sudoku junkie and got hooked on the free version of this last year. I don't know why I didn't buy this sooner! The easy ones are very easy with half being solvable in 20 seconds ("Easiest") to 2 minutes ("Difficult"). The real fun is in trying to beat the top 5 most difficult, from "Ridiculous" to "maelstrom", in the fastest time of the day. All 15 levels are new every day but only the paid version has a library of all 15 levels. Enjoy!
Great application I'll enjoy this for hours, thanks.

It handles sudoku perfectly, with options that make it easy for any style of play. The hints don't come unless you really want them (two separate clicks), but when you need them they're there - and they come in two parts, one pointing where to look and one showing you exactly what the next step is. New games every day (as many as you want), at assorted difficulty levels, and you can put in your own games as well. The only thing it doesn't handle is Sudoku Monster, a 4x4 grid (rather than the standard 3x3).

Great for regular play; even better if you want improve.  They make it easy by giving you the option to drill further into the hints.  This is my fourth Sudoku App and my first-keeper.  It's made me a better player over the few years I've had it.  LOVE IT!

I've played Sudoku puzzles for years now. I started playing them the old-fashioned way, with a pencil, eraser and a puzzle book. I then graduated to playing them digitally, first on pc, and then the tablet. As a regular player I've always been on a look out for the best Sudoku apps: the apps that recreate the magic I've experienced playing them on paper. I've gone through quite a few of them in the app market, testing out the most highly rated, most downloaded apps. Some left me cold, others don't work quite right. Until the day I downloaded Enjoy Sudoku... the search is over, or nearly. It has thoughtful design, great UI, and is buttery smooth in gameplay. Plus, the one thing that attracted me most about this app is its superb puzzle generator, which guarantees limitless replayability. I'd be hard pressed to find any fault with this app. [**For the next update, I hope the author will enable players to have multiple saved states, instead of a single save. Sometimes, being able to start a new game with the chance of returning to the previous unsolved toughie is helpful.**] If you're going to buy a Sudoku app, make it this one. It has all the features you ever need to 'Enjoy Sudoku'.
